summary:
The Security Council,
Recalling previous resolutions on Western Sahara, 
Reaffirming commitment to assist parties to achieve a just, lasting and mutually acceptable political solution providing for self-determination of the people of Western Sahara,
Reiterating call for cooperation to end the impasse and achieve progress towards a political solution,
Urging POLISARIO Front to release prisoners of war, 
Calling upon Morocco and POLISARIO Front to cooperate with the International Committee of the Red Cross,
Having considered the Secretary-General's report,
1. Extends MINURSO mandate until 31 October 2005;
2. Affirms need for full respect of military agreements with MINURSO;
3. Calls on Member States to consider voluntary contributions for Confidence Building Measures;
4. Awaits comprehensive review of MINURSO's structure;
5. Requests Secretary-General's report on Western Sahara before mandate end;
6. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
